      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNCLE TONY (4) did a good job to be beaten less than 2m as runner-up from a similar barrier last week. That put the writing on the wall so can go one better. WILLIAMS (8) has come from wider on this row for two strong efforts since heading north, working to find find the front before going on for a 1.6m win at Redcliffe last week. Draws for a trail and has yet to miss a place in six tries at this distance, winning twice. RACE FOR RICHES (11) progressed off a second here two back before scoring last start by 3 metres at venue, both from this row. Draws wider but is going well. MY ULTIMATE COSSIE (3) has won the last two times he has raced here, racing wide in the latter stages last week and digging deep. Up in grade but draws for another strong showing. COSMIC FLYER (6) is going well enough to make an impact with even luck from a  wide draw.",
